caption: The food is amazing!!

Horrible. Horrible. Horrible. The bartender was rude and very snobby. I only ordered 2 drinks and she acted like I asked her to run a mile. I did not tip. Not even a minute after sitting down outside does a man storm out and scream at my husband for not tipping. My husband calmly apologized and tried to explain but the man just yelled and threw my receipt in his face. We have never experienced something so rude. 1 star is to much.
Great service but the staff seems overworked.
Do not order here to-go, they decline all takeout orders when they feel like they are "busy."

Got sick off of their food last night and the medium burger my boyfriend ordered came out raw and cold. The food was disgusting and, even though I only ate half of it, I've been throwing up all day because of it. Someone needs to send the health inspector in. None of their employees are wearing masks and there was a little kid running in and out of the kitchen. Who does that? It's a dive.

This place has a very hard working staff. They welcome you and your best friend. Mine is a Chihuahua. The food is very good and they even remember what you like to drink. Go by, say Hello and tell them Russell sent you.

This has to be the worst managed restaurant in Tampa. Zero awareness when it comes to customer service. They are lucky local residents have limited options... some advice to management —> when everyone in the room is telling you you’re crazy
Bad service Order took over 30 minutes My nachos look like the local lunch lady prepared it....
Bad service, even worse food.
We were having too much fun. Can't post photos.  Here's a pic of a burger that looks like the one we had. Lol! Seriously, food, staff and the Manhattan's... =)
Good atmosphere and delicious food. Fair prices and a good service!
Love this place! The breakfast burrito is perfect! Very chill vibes.

We were at Late Start Brewing having a beer and wanted some Mexican food. We were not disappointed. Server was super friendly and let us move tables because we didn't realize people could smoke outside so we went inside in the atmosphere in the bar has really chill vibe. Food was great and a decent drink selection. They also sell liquor so that's convenient. Definitely worth a visit.

Giving this place two stars only because of the decent food. Service has been horrendous the last couple times. Same bartender both times and I gave her the BOTD because maybe she had a bad day last time, but this time it was poor service again. Obviously not happy to be there, took forever to take drink orders while she looked right at us and carried on a long convo with co-workers and then when she finally came over she was just plain rude.

Stop by for a quick drink and I ask what specials they have the bartender told me none. So I order Michelob ultra, went to the bathroom and saw a sign Bud light specials. I am not happy. My glass is not fill with Bud light.
Great food
The service was very good and the food was good too

This place is super interesting. Definitely a local watering hole which is great. They’ve got several TV’s and the bartenders don’t get annoyed at my bf and I for asking to watch obscure college football games... as long as one TV has on the Lightening, if they’re playing.  The service is fantastic and they have a great tequila selection. And they always seem to have on classic rock which is always a plus for me as well.
Awesome place to chill and have drink we came to late for food but im sure the food is great like the service thanks guys!!!!
Not good.

I ate here once with my coworkers and I immediately started getting sick before I even left the restaurant. My best guess is that the beer was bad/spoiled and all of the sriracha sauces had turned to a dark color
Those girl's ROCK they know how to hustle & they're all pretty too!! I love goin City Dog. Their burritoes are HUGE & delicious both of em!!
Enjoyed my experience here! Friendly staff, full bar, and awesome food menu.
Great food and customer service. Awesome staff thanks Jenny

Great place to eat! Just moved here and walked over, waitress was super nice, responsive, observant, but not overly attentive. Super cute bar with a crazy amount of food and drink options. Food and drinks were really good too!  The only negatives were that I thought the portion was a little bit small for the price, but given the location I think it’s fitting.  I also wish they used single use menus, were more through with their cleaning of the reusable ones, or had a QR code with the full menu for us to look at on our phones.  I’ll definitely be back again! 😁
Amazing place, good food and great service

Mexican downtown restaurant. Oddly enough, my favorite menu items are the fajitas salad and their take on a seasoned burger. The fries are super thin and crispy (the way they should be) and come with some type of house-made dipping sauce that’s really good. Hours of operation can be tricky so check before you go.

Absolutely love this place! Ambiance is amazing, true spirited local hotspot and true Tampa Channel District neighborhood favorite hotspot for great eats, great drinks, selection, the friendliest crowd and people the owner is fabulous, amazingly creatively decorated, cool Collectibles everywhere highly recommend! Check them out after visiting Maven Market second Saturdays or other days during the week! Love frequenting this place!

City Dog Cantina rules, Maloney’s Irish Pub drools. The bartenders here greeted us immediately, as where the bartender at Maloney’s completely ignored us until we decided to leave; apparently we weren’t important enough to interrupt her complaining about a customer that had just left. The food, drinks, and bartenders are great at City Dog. “The Dog” drink is phenomenal! Thank you Micha and Nicole!

Admitted didn't try anything but beer here, but the staff was friendly and approachable, and what I saw of the menu looked reasonably priced (with a few even cheaper options so your thrifty friends can come along too).  Very relaxed atmosphere, and most of the booths has access to a wall port so you could plug in your phone if needed (and yes, we needed).  They also sell bottles of liquor to go that are chilled, which was something I had never seen before where I'm from.

Food rocks! Creative menu, service is awesome. The bartenders a super chill, this place will never disappoint. I love the breakfast taco or the loaded nachos and their tequila specials!
Nice local joint
They have a streak burrito that is delicious and I hear everything is made in house. Very delicious cantina!
Local watering hole for many of the residents. Good clean atmosphere but doesn’t feel like a “fake chain”. They have an extensive bar list, with reasonable prices.  Good bar, good vibes.

Mainly a bar, but they have a small dining area. The lobster bite tacos were great and the shrimp burrito was as well. The jalapeño carrots weren't what we expected. They were raw carrot slices with vinegar and jalapeños. Still good. Service was good.

If you happen to be in the Channelside area and you don't have one of their suspiciously strong Frozés, you're doing it wrong! Excellent brunch menu, and very affordable. It's no wonder they attract such a large crowd every weekend! What a great way to start your Sunday or Parade day in Tampa!
The girl who served us was awesome and their buffalo shrimp was delicous. Plus u can watch sports while youre at the bar or at a table

The food is usually pretty good. Beer selection leaves a lot to be desired. I'm not sure what's going on with the bartenders in there, but they always seem to be robotic and a bit unhappy. Usually not too busy and has a good atmosphere overall.
We stopped by after a concert and so glad we did! Delicious food, large portions, great price and excellent service. Highly recommend this place for a game, a drink and a bite!
Good food

The food wasn't out of this world spectacular, but it was really good! Jack, our server was very attentive, and extra polite.  I had a great dinner with my wife, I don't understand the negative reviews, I thought the place was awesome, the food hit the spot, and I was very pleased with my whole experience. To make it 5 star the food could be a little more delicious, but it was still great.
Fun place to sit outside, enjoy music and pet pups!! The wings were really YUM!
The staff is incredible. So accommodating. Very friendly. One of my favorite go-to bars in Tampa.

I have visited the Catina several times, say 10 times during lunch and ordered the seasoned burger with fries. The burger came on a toasted brioche bun and a delicious fat burger. It always take 30-40 minutes for the food to arrive. Same thing today and pictures that the place is practically empty. WHY? The last 3 visits the burger changed, the toasted brioche bun is gone and replaced with a cheap McD bun and a smaller burger to match the bun. The only thing that didn’t change was the exorbitant long wait time for an empty cafe. For a $12 burger they need to step it up.

Disappointing. Over priced. The bar didn’t know how to make half of basic drinks, I ordered a caprese salad. And is not how a caprese salad is supposed to be like. Another person in my group ordered a chicken quesadillla. They brought her a quesadilla with no chicken. She said something and they brought her a chicken breast. I’m guessing they expected her to cut the chicken and stuff it in the already glued together with melted cheese quesadilla? Smh.. not impressed. For the price, the food quality is not up to par.
Staff was AWESOME with our large group. Place was clean looking. Price to food quality wasn't great, bit on the heavy side of cost. Possible a rent thing, being in a trendy location.

The food was the only saving grace of our experience. All of the tables were dirty so we sat anyway. The waitress came to clean the table and sprayed my arms with the chemicals. Instead of pointing into the rag she directly sprayed the table and us. Our waitress who was taking care of us finally came over and gave us our drinks and then we didn't see her for 15 minutes. She walked by looking at us but took her sweet time taking our orders. My companion  was on his lunch break and only gets an hour. It people come for lunch you need to be mindful of their time. Other than our crappy waitress the food was good but not worth the wait. It's great if you're drunk I'm sure.

Today we sat outside for 10 minutes unnoticed moved inside and ordered the food came out fast but our waitress was on her phone and not aware of what was going on around her. My wife even.watched her look up at us and go back to her phone

I am not fond of Bar food since typically it's crappy, under seasoned and Mediocre. Came here and had the best burger of my life full of flavor, my wife had a BLT which was so far from ordinary. The bacon is perfectly cooked thick and the cilantro aoli has a kick that is delicious. I highly recommend this bar!
Its pretty good food. Some items very salty!
Worst service I have ever experienced. The wait staff is slow and un-attentive. Three stars for the food and affordable prices but they should focus more on customer service.
Staff is always very prompt and friendly. Food is fresh and interesting.
Food was delicious. I loved the hummus, and the chicken tacos, and potato tacos were incredible.

i love their bacon breakfast quesadillas and their shrimp burittos. they're big enough to split. i have eaten here often. their salsa is a little lacking and they don't give you a lot of chips with your order. i don't recommend their philly cheesesteak sandwich here. their nachos are huge! drinks are kind of pricey here! Service is kind of hit or miss. Sometimes it can be very slow and other times it can be quick. Lots of turn-around with the servers.

Nice decor and good food for a full liquor bar. The atmosphere just really isn't my thing. I guess you can't blame the bar for the type of customers that frequent the establishment. But both times I have been the patrons just seem like a bunch of "meat heads" on steroids. The service has been pretty pour both times also, with the bar staff engaging the regulars and ignoring the other customers. Not my thing, but see for yourself.

Worst customer service. We told the waiter we were vegetarian and ordered a jalapeño mac and cheese and said no bacon. The waitress brought the mac and cheese with bacon. After we told her we said no bacon she said she would have to charge again for the Mac and cheese. She stated that this is the owners policy. This is the first restaurant I have ever been too that has ever done that. If you go just know that even if your order is wrong they won't change it. Poor customer service! Wish we could give it 0 stars.
Been coming here for a while for drinks and meals. Great brunch choices for the weekend and never disappoints during the week. Can't go wrong with the fajita burger.
Another hidden gem in the area. Nice area and great place to drink.

I am giving a 3 star review because this is a cool spot for drinks and nice atmosphere, but the food just grosses me out. They have good breakfast tacos on the weekend and delicious coffee/alcohol drinks, but other than that...the food is not very good. Too much seasoning, salty, and greasy. Nothing seems fresh. The staff is pretty cool, but more of a rough around the edges personality, which is fun but not personable.
Place is solid.  Their pickled carrots are the jam.  You will not be mad you ate here.
Twice had a really good burrito!

Focus on burritos, but not really a Mexican restaurant.  My wife got the grilled cheese and tomato soup and it was very good.  Loads of gooey cheese.  I had their chicken fajita salad, which was very filling for a salad.  Good selection of draft beer and mixed drinks, a few TVs fit into the relaxed atmosphere.  There is outside seating with umbrellas but it was way too hot for that.
Great burrito.

I was there the same morning of the most recent bad review, and would have to completely disagree with that review of the server, Courtney. While yes, the service was slow and the food lagged to come out, she was the only server on and had every single seat full inside, outside, and at the bar.  It was the day after Gasparilla, and brought in way more customers than normal. Not only did Courtney apologize for the delay in service and food, she happily took our orders without writing them down and delivered hot, delicious, and correct food when it was ready.  While it wasn't the quickest turnaround, there is some common sense to be taken into account here and not reflective of a bad restaurant, just bad circumstances. Every other customer there seemed to understand the situation and would simply cash out their checks if the service was not in their time table.

3 reviews for 5 star??? U gotta be kidding me!! Went there this morning to try them out and it took them 50 minutes to be exact for our breakfast to be served. There's only two of us on the table mind you.  It wasn't like there's 6 of us who has complicated order. The waitress was lousy!!! She looked like she felt obligated to work there. No life nor even a smile on her face when serving customers. Asked her 3x for coffee and my boyfriend finally stood up for the 4th time to get the word enter her head. Asked her why the food took forever and all she can say was "don't know", not even an apology for forgetting the coffee or food being served late. She's like a dead fish!!  She's not writing down orders from customers which screwed up my order!!  Her service is a bad representation of the restaurant. I think the manager or owner need to take customer service 101 class to know how to serve customer or survive in the service business to better train their employees. I won't go back there ever again!!!!!! And will spread the word to my Channelside neighbors. These residents deserve better.
Great food, great service!! Will go back for sure.

Excellent food. Everything on the menu I have tasted is good to great, especially the chicken sandwich. Our entire office visits this place regularly (since we work above it) and we have yet to tire of their food and drinks.
